.TH SUTURE-RESET "1" "April 2026" "Suture v5.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
suture\-reset \- Reset HEAD to a specific commit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B suture reset [\\fIoptions\\fR] \\fItarget\\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reset HEAD to a specific commit.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \\\-m, \\\-\\\-mode \\fI<mode>\\fR
Reset mode: soft, mixed, hard (default: mixed)
.TP
.BR \\\-C \\fI<REPO_PATH>\\fR
Run as if suture was started in <path>
.TP
.BR \\\-h, \\\-\\\-help
Print help
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
suture reset HEAD~1        # Reset to parent (mixed mode)
suture reset abc123 \\\-\\\-soft  # Keep changes staged
suture reset abc123 \\\-\\\-hard  # Discard all changes
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR suture (1)
